            . I am a <rs id="t18300916-55-viclabel292" type="occupation">horse-keeper</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18300916-55-victim556 t18300916-55-viclabel292"></join>. On the 5th of May I slept at Mr. Battersey's, the <placeName id="t18300916-55-crimeloc293">Ship, in Long-acre</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18300916-55-crimeloc293" type="placeName" value="Ship, in Long-acre"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18300916-55-crimeloc293" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18300916-55-off290 t18300916-55-crimeloc293"></join> - the prisoner was billeted there, and slept in the same room; my coat was in that room, and the half-crowns and handkerchiefs were in a box that was locked. I got up early in the morning of the 5th of May, and went out, leaving these things secure; when I returned at nine o'clock at night, the prisoner and the property were gone - he had been there six weeks or two months; I got my coat at Windsor about the 17th of August - the prisoner was there then; he is in the Grenadier Guards - the serjeant wrote to the landlord on the 13th of August, and I went down on the 17th; my box had been broken open.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18300916-55-person558">
                  MARK 
                  JONES
